Word clouds











In [44]:



     


#function for generating word cloud
def word_cloud_build(data,m,w,h):

    t = " ".join(review for review in data)

    word_cloud = WordCloud(background_color='black',stopwords = STOPWORDS, max_font_size=m,
                           random_state = 42,width=w,height=h).generate(t)
    
    return word_cloud

In [7]:



     


def dict_word_count(data,n):

    word_count_d = defaultdict(int)

    for review in data:
        for word in build_grams(review,n):
            word_count_d[word] += 1

    df = pd.DataFrame(sorted(word_count_d.items(), key=lambda x: x[1])[::-1])
    df.columns = ["word", "frequency"]
    
    return df



     















In [27]:



     


#reference: https://www.kaggle.com/code/sudalairajkumar/simple-exploration-notebook-qiqc
def build_grams(review, n):
    word = [word for word in review.lower().split(" ") if word != "" if word not in STOPWORDS]
    return [" ".join(out) for out in zip(*[word[i:] for i in range(n)])]

#function for plotting
def custom_bar_chart(df, col):
    chart = go.Bar(y=df["word"].values[::-1], x=df["frequency"].values[::-1],
                   showlegend=False, orientation = 'h',marker=dict(color=col,))
    
    return chart 

#function for subplots
def subplots(titles,r,c,fig_1,fig_2,h,w,hs,sup_title):
    
    fig = plotly.subplots.make_subplots(rows=r, cols=c, vertical_spacing=0.04,
                              horizontal_spacing=hs,subplot_titles= titles)
    
    fig.append_trace(fig_1, r, r)
    fig.append_trace(fig_2, r, c)

    fig['layout'].update(height=h, width=w, title=sup_title)
    py.iplot(fig)
    
    return
